        "description": "In-vitro hemolysis experiments must be conducted with bovine blood at hematocrit 38 ± 2% and temperature 37 ± 0.5 °C; all five COU2 operating points must be covered; measurement uncertainty on hemolysis index must be reported and < 10% of measured value."
      },
      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments performed at FDA CDRH laboratory using fresh bovine blood (hematocrit 38.5 ± 1.2%, temperature 37.0 ± 0.3 °C). All five operating points tested in triplicate. Modified Index of Hemolysis (MIH) measured via plasma-free hemoglobin photometry; measurement uncertainty 4.8–7.3% across operating points. Conditions fully documented in FDA test report TF-2024-0312. Achieved Gradation 5."
    },
