        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria — COU2",
        "description": "Turbulence model selection must be justified against PIV velocity field data for the FDA pump; SST k-ω model must predict mean velocity within 10% RMSE compared to PIV measurements; hemolysis power-law model coefficients must be sourced from peer-reviewed literature with documented uncertainty bounds."
      },
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on published FDA pump round-robin study results (Stewart et al. 2012, Hariharan et al. 2011). PIV comparison at 3500 RPM / 3 L/min: velocity RMSE = 7.3% of bulk velocity. Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model coefficients (α = 3.62×10⁻⁷, β = 2.416, γ = 0.785) sourced from Taskin et al. 2012 with ±15% coefficient uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo. Model form selection documented in analysis plan AP-COU2-v3. Gradation 4 achieved."
    },
