      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou2/ac/model-inputs",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria — COU2",
        "description": "All material properties (blood density, Carreau-Yasuda viscosity parameters) and operating boundary conditions must have documented uncertainty distributions; input uncertainty must be propagated through the model via Monte Carlo with ≥ 1000 samples; input sensitivity indices (Sobol first-order) must be reported."
      },
      "rationale": "Six uncertain inputs identified: blood density (ρ = 1056 ± 10 kg/m³, normal), four Carreau-Yasuda parameters (λ, n, μ₀, μ∞ — normal distributions from literature), and inlet flow rate (± 0.05 L/min, uniform). Monte Carlo with 2000 Latin Hypercube samples propagated through surrogate model (Kriging, R² = 0.997). Sobol first-order indices computed: flow rate (S₁ = 0.41) and μ₀ (S₁ = 0.29) dominate hemolysis index variance. Input uncertainty contribution documented in UQ report UQ-COU2-2025. Gradation 4 achieved."
