        "description": "Hemolysis experiments must be conducted in triplicate at each operating point using blood from at least two independent donors; inter-donor variability must be reported and incorporated into the experimental uncertainty estimate."
      },
      "rationale": "Experiments conducted in triplicate at all five operating points using pooled bovine blood from three independent donations (lot numbers BV-2024-041, BV-2024-055, BV-2024-063). Inter-donor coefficient of variation for MIH: 6.8–9.4% across operating points. Donor variability incorporated into experimental uncertainty as an additional normal random variable in the Monte Carlo UQ framework. Sample preparation and handling documented per ASTM F1830. Gradation 3 achieved."
