        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Equivalency of input parameters acceptance criteria — COU2",
        "description": "Simulation boundary conditions must be matched to experimental conditions within ± 2% for flow rate and ± 1% for rotational speed; any remaining discrepancies must be assessed for their impact on hemolysis index via sensitivity analysis."
      },
      "rationale": "Simulation boundary conditions set to match experimental values within 0.8% for flow rate and 0.3% for rotational speed across all five operating points. Residual discrepancies assessed via one-at-a-time perturbation: ± 2% flow rate perturbation produces ± 3.1% change in hemolysis index (within combined uncertainty). Temperature equivalency confirmed: simulation at 37 °C matches experimental 37.0 ± 0.3 °C. Full equivalency mapping documented in EQ-COU2-v2. Gradation 4 achieved."
